N:vercel-react-best-practices
D:React and Next.js performance optimization guidelines from Vercel Engineering. Use when writing, reviewing, or refactoring React and Next.js code for waterfalls, bundle size, caching, rendering, and re-render performance.
G:react next.js nextjs vercel performance optimization waterfalls bundle-size rsc suspense dynamic-import cache rendering
F:Claude|ChatGPT|Gemini
T:Read|Write|Edit

U[5]:
  Review React or Next.js code for performance regressions
  Eliminate data-fetch waterfalls with Promise.all and Suspense
  Reduce bundle size with direct imports and dynamic loading
  Improve server and client caching patterns for repeated requests
  Refactor rendering and state updates to reduce unnecessary re-renders

S[4]{n,action,details}:
  1,Inspect,Read the target components or routes and identify the slow path category first
  2,Prioritize,Fix CRITICAL waterfall and bundle issues before lower-priority rendering cleanups
  3,Refactor,Apply the Vercel guideline that matches the concrete bottleneck
  4,Verify,Check loading behavior, bundle impact, and rendering results after the change

R[4]:
  Prefer parallel fetching over sequential await chains for independent work
  Avoid barrel imports when direct imports reduce bundle size
  Keep server-to-client serialization minimal across RSC boundaries
  Use transitions, caching, and dynamic imports only where they solve a real bottleneck
